Clayton Dubilier May Bid for Aviva’s RAC, Sunday Times Says

-- B y   A g n e s   L o v a s z
-- 
2011-04-17T09:38:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-17/clayton-dubilier-may-bid-for-aviva-s-rac-sunday-times-says.html
Clayton, Dubilier & Rice LLC is
considering a bid for  Aviva Plc (AV/) ’s RAC roadside recovery service,
the Sunday Times reported, without saying how it got the
information.  Aviva, which paid 1.1 billion pounds ($1.8 billion) for the
business in 2005, hired JPMorgan Chase & Co to manage the sale,
the newspaper reported. Other bidders may include  Carlyle Group ,
according to the Sunday Times.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Agnes Lovasz at 
